  "id": "019d298e-98d1-7341-b83d-b83e19ca3fd8",
  "content": "# GPU Monitoring + Inference Health — Implementation Complete (2026-03-26)\n\nPR #9 (feat/gpu-monitoring-inference-health) implements corvia#5 and corvia#6.\n\n## 9 commits, 3 crates changed:\n- corvia-common: GpuProcess, InferenceHealthStatus, InferenceProbeStatus types; health_probe_interval_secs + drift_threshold config\n- corvia-proto: HealthResponse extended with 8 new fields (ep_name through last_probe_at)\n- corvia-inference: probe.rs module with canary, periodic probe loop, TOCTOU-safe init, JoinHandle stored\n- corvia-server: NVIDIA power/process metrics, intel_gpu_top integration, 5s cache with stampede guard, gRPC Health() integration\n\n## Key implementation details:\n- embed_canary() helper added to EmbeddingServiceImpl to bypass tonic wrapping\n- Canary triggers in LoadModel handler on first embedding model (not server boot)\n- ProbeState uses tokio::sync::RwLock; write-lock CAS prevents race on concurrent LoadModel\n- nvidia-smi stays CSV (not XML) with 3s timeout; separate --query-compute-apps for processes\n- intel_gpu_top spawned with SIGKILL in all paths; binary existence checked first\n- GpuMetricsCache uses refreshing flag for stampede protection",
